data.name: Papa-Figo
data.description: A high-performance handgun with an ingenious, elegant design. Named after a mythical monster said to devour disobedient children, according to its creator.

data.name: Classified Manuscript
data.description: A high-performance SMG, a powerful and unique weapon. When he gave it this name, the designer probably intended it to be a secret weapon.

data.name: Arcana
data.description: High-performance sniper rifle with a cold and technological appearance. Does the bullet's trajectory also embody the principles of the universe's operation?

data.name: Guerno
data.description: A high-performance assault rifle capable of easily adapting to various combat scenarios. Named after the Valkyrie Guerno, it likely yearns to be wielded by those of noble character.

data.name: Crowned Jackalope
data.description: A high-performance melee weapon, immensely powerful with an artistic design. Battles fought with this weapon would undoubtedly be a spectacle to behold.

data.name: Mjölnir
data.description: A high-performance machine gun notable for its exceptional capacity and formidable power. The designer's choice of name suggests a hope that users might wield its power with the aptitude of Thor himself.

data.name: Expeditionary Pigeon
data.description: A powerful shotgun with sleek lines and tremendous force. With such power, even timid young pigeons might regain their courage and bravely protect their companions.

data.name: Retired UMP9
data.description: A low-cost weapon commonly found in contamination zones. Its stock shows some damage, and numerous welding marks are visible across the gun's frame.

data.name: UMP9
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Lenna. Modified based on her combat preferences. Ensures high shooting accuracy despite the increased rate of fire.

data.name: Löwenjunges
data.description: A high-performance submachine gun assigned to Lenna. Its modifications are based on the UMP9. Leva's opinions were also considered during the modification process, and Lenna likes this gun very much.

data.name: Retired KSVK
data.description: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Poor maintenance has affected its shooting accuracy, so this gun can only be used in a pinch.

data.name: KSVK
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Dushevnaya. Modified based on her preferences in combat. Features varying degrees of improvement to both penetration and shooting accuracy.

data.name: Eulogistic Verse
data.description: A high-performance rifle assigned to Dushevnaya. Based on the KSVK, reducing recoil without compromising power. "It speaks to me in a profound way, perhaps as a heroic verse that continues to shine even after a thousand years," says Dushevnaya.

data.name: Retired Three-Line Rifle M1891
data.description: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Its style is outdated, but it is still sturdy and functional.

data.name: Three-Line Rifle M1891
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Mosin-Nagant. Modified based on her combat preferences. Its streamlined design facilitates easy maintenance and handling.

data.name: Samosek
data.description: A high-performance rifle assigned to Mosin-Nagant. Based on the original Three-line Rifle M1891. While retaining its versatility, its power has been pushed to the limit. When Mosin-Nagant raises the rifle and takes aim at the enemy, is she also examining her own heart?

data.name: Retired W 2000
data.description: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Its frame has some dents, but it doesn't affect the firing efficiency.

data.name: W 2000
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Makiatto. Modified based on her combat preferences. Features include lighter weight and improved shooting accuracy.

data.name: Bittersweet Caramel
data.description: A high-performance rifle assigned to Makiatto. Based on the W 2000. It has undergone countless adjustments to achieve ultimate precision and power. Makiatto wields this weapon to break through all obstacles, infusing her simmering emotions into each bullet.

data.name: Retired Type 97
data.description: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Appears worn-out, as if it could break at any moment if not handled with care.

data.name: Type 97
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Jiangyu. Modified based on her combat preferences. The reinforced body structure and significant power boost have made it more robust and potent.

data.name: Leaping Tiger
data.description: A high-performance assault rifle assigned to Jiangyu, based on the Type 97, is an exceptionally reliable weapon. The sound of bullets leaving the barrel is sharp and lively, reminiscent of rousing drumbeats in a musical piece, making it one of Jiangyu's favorites.

data.name: Retired Stechkin
data.description: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. This gun is a bit old and can barely hit the target.

data.name: Stechkin
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Ksenia. Modified based on her combat preferences. Features a lighter frame and improved accuracy.

data.name: Retired Pluma Edge
data.description: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. While plain and old-fashioned in appearance, it can still be frequently encountered in the contamination zones.

data.name: Pluma Edge
data.description: A melee weapon, highly compatible with Ullrid. It has been modified in accordance with her preferences in combat, and is exceedingly sharp and durable.

data.name: Rectrix
data.description: A high-performance melee weapon assigned to Ullrid. Exquisitely forged out of high-quality steel whilst adorned with simple floral decorations, this weapon's appearance appears both keen and swift.

data.name: Retired Model ARM
data.description: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Somewhat heavy, but overall still reasonably easy to carry.

data.name: Model ARM
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Littara. Modified based on her combat preferences, making it more suitable for harsh environments and comfortable to use.

data.name: Retired Suomi
data.description: A cheap weapon from an underground broker. It is scratched and worn all over its frame, but it doesn't affect the gun's function.

data.name: Suomi
data.description: A firearm that is highly compatible with Suomi. It has been modified to suit Suomi's fighting style. Reducing the gun's weight has also increased its durability and firepower.

data.name: Unspoken Calling
data.description: A high-performance submachine gun issued to Suomi. Modelled after the Suomi, it is both lighter and more powerful than its original, and it is suitable for various complex combat conditions. With this gun, Suomi will accomplish all the missions given to her.

data.name: Retired PPSh-41
data.description: A cheap weapon from an underground broker. The frame is mottled and discolored, but it's still solid and reliable.

data.name: PPSh-41
data.description: A firearm that is highly compatible with Papasha. It has been modified to suit Papasha's fighting style. While the material is still the same, its frame is more solid.

data.name: Svarog
data.description: A high-performance submachine gun issued to Papasha. Modelled after the PPSh, it is lighter than the original while still retaining its predecessor's firepower and low recoil. Papasha holds it high, showing its glorious light off to all.

data.name: Retired M1 Super 90
data.description: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Its performance and appearance are both equally unremarkable.

data.name: M1 Super 90
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Lotta, it has been modified to suit Lotta's fighting style. The power and endurance has been significantly boosted.

data.name: Retired G36K-KSK
data.description: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. It's really old and worn out, and looks like it's reaching the upper limit of it's lifespan.

data.name: G36K-KSK
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Andoris. Modified based on her combat preferences, it features improved firepower and error correction.

data.name: Aglaea
data.description: A high-performance assault rifle assigned to Andoris. Based on the G36K-KSK. It is easy to handle, reliable, and has improved firepower. With this in hand, Andoris gains the confidence to protect those she views as important.

data.name: Retired Skoda 75
data.description: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. There are some problems with the firing mechanism, but one must make do with what they have.

data.name: Skoda 75
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Faye. Modified based on her combat preferences, it is durable, light and easy to handle.

data.name: Hestia
data.description: A high-performance handgun assigned to Faye. Based on the Skoda 75, it is convenient to carry, reliable, precise and accurate. In Faye's hands, Hestia becomes as fearsome as a true Goddess of Flame.

data.name: Retired Ksvec .45 ACP
data.description: An old weapon commonly seen in the contaminated zones. It's about to completely fall apart, but can still be used if you are careful enough.

data.name: Ksvec .45 ACP
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Vector. Modified based on her combat preferences, it is highly maneuverable and stable.

data.name: Banshee's Whisper
data.description: A high-performance submachine gun assigned to Vector. Based on the Ksvec .45 ACP, it has been completely overhauled. Pull the trigger, and let death whisper a song into the ears of enemies.

data.name: Retired Sturmgewehr 28
data.description: An old weapon commonly seen in the contaminated zones. It shows a high degree of erosion by the elements.

data.name: Sturmgewehr 28
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Belka. Modified based on her combat preferences, it is now even more suited for long-range shooting.

data.name: Sylvan Elf
data.description: A high-performance assault rifle assigned to Belka. Based on the Sturmgewehr 28, it has been further improved in terms of shooting accuracy, precision and firepower. She bounces around the battlefield like an elf in a forest, pushing back intruders with agility and precision.

data.name: Retired Springfield
data.description: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. It’s not very stable or reliable, but can still be used, more or less.

data.name: Springfield
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Springfield. Modified based on her combat preferences, it provides increased bullet velocity, hence improving firepower.

data.name: Radiance
data.description: A high-performance rifle assigned to Springfield. Based on the Springfield, it has been further improved in terms of carrying convenience and firing speed. Pierce through all adversity, to carve out a brighter future for those you deem important.

data.name: Retired CS/LS06
data.description: A cheap weapon from an underground broker. Its barrel is a little rusty, and its lethality is in question.

data.name: CS/LS06
data.description: A firearm that is highly compatible with Zhaohui. It has been modified to suit Zhaohui's fighting style. It's lighter and handier, improving its accuracy on the move.

data.name: Juggernaut
data.description: A high-performance submachine gun issued to Zhaohui. Modelled after the CS/LS06, its lethality has been greatly increased, making it a blade of righteousness for a chivalrous warrior. "A man slain with but a step and slash, A journey unending for a thousand miles."

data.name: Retired G11
data.description: An old weapon commonly seen in the contaminated zones. It is tattered and worn, but can still be used.

data.name: G11
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Mechty. Modified based on her combat preferences, it has improved rate of fire, precision and accuracy.

data.name: Daydream
data.description: A high-performance assault rifle assigned to Mechty. Based on the G11, its firepower has been further improved. A gun that complements Mechty's burst-firing nature, it is dedicated to shattering the daydreams of enemies.

data.name: Retired 416
data.description: An old weapon commonly seen in the contaminated zones. It looks old, but the damage to it is minimal and it can be used normally.
A firearm that is highly compatible with Klukai. It has been modified to suit Klukai's fighting style, granting it a significant increase in reliability and accuracy.

data.name: Skylla
data.description: A high-performance assault rifle issued to Klukai, modelled after the 416. Its flexibility has been greatly increased, making it suitable for various combat tactics. Its perfect appearance and performance belies its rampant ambition, and its fangs will tear all foes to shreds.

data.name: Hare
data.description: A melee weapon highly compatible with Krolik. Modified based on her combat preferences and painted with a skin that matches Krolik's colors.

data.name: Retired .380 Curva
data.description: Colphne's designated training weapon. Frequently used in team coordination drills as well as for basic combat operations when necessary.

data.name: Retired .50 Nemesis
data.description: Nemesis' designated training weapon. Frequently used in team coordination drills as well as for basic combat operations when necessary.

data.name: Retired OTs-14
data.description: Groza's designated training weapon. Frequently used in team coordination drills as well as for basic combat operations when necessary.

data.name: .50 Nemesis
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Nemesis. Modified based on her combat preferences. Features further improved firepower and accuracy.

data.name: .380 Curva
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Colphne. Modified based on her combat preferences. The modifications make it practical, compact, and easy to use, while also enhancing its power.

data.name: Heart Seeker
data.description: A high-performance shotgun assigned to Vepley. Based on the Vepr-12. Designed to protect the audience in case of unexpected incidents during her performances. However, as a professional idol, Vepley might use this gun to secretly capture the hearts of her fans.

data.name: Retired Vepr-12
data.description: Vepley's designated training weapon. Frequently used in team coordination drills as well as for basic combat operations when necessary.

data.name: Optical Illusion
data.description: A high-performance machine gun assigned to Peritya. Based on the Pecheneg-SP. After modifications, its power has been significantly enhanced. Will the one wielding this weapon also vanish like an illusion?

data.name: Vepr-12
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Vepley. Modified based on her combat preferences, making it a "performance prop" more suitable for cute and energetic idols.

data.name: Retired Hare
data.description: Krolik's designated training weapon. Frequently used in team coordination drills as well as for basic combat operations when necessary.

data.name: OTs-14
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Groza. Modified based on her combat preferences. Features improved firepower and burst fire effectiveness while ensuring that it's still easy to carry.

data.name: Retired Pecheneg-SP
data.description: Peritya's designated training weapon. Frequently used in team coordination drills as well as for basic combat operations when necessary.

data.name: Pecheneg-SP
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Peritya. Modified based on her combat preferences. Features improved firepower and portability, becoming more potent in Peritya's hands.

data.name: Retired Robinson Modular Rifle
data.description: Sharkry's designated training weapon. Frequently used in team coordination drills as well as for basic combat operations when necessary.

data.name: Robinson Modular Rifle
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Sharkry. Modified based on her combat preferences. Features improved overall balance and enhanced shooting precision.

data.name: Retired Model Alpha
data.description: Tololo's designated training weapon. Frequently used in team coordination drills as well as for basic combat operations when necessary.

data.name: Model Alpha
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Tololo. Modified based on her combat preferences. improving shooting accuracy and adapting it to various combat environments.

data.name: Planeta
data.description: A high-performance assault rifle assigned to Tololo. Based on the Model Alpha. Features include lighter frame and higher shooting accuracy. Its lightweight, innovative design combines pragmatic rationality with the romance of exploring the unknown, much like its owner.

data.name: Retired MP7H1
data.description: Cheeta's designated training weapon. Frequently used in team coordination drills as well as for basic combat operations when necessary.

data.name: MP7H1
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Cheeta. Modified based on her combat preferences. Offers substantial firepower despite featuring a small and extremely light frame.

data.name: Retired QBZ-191
data.description: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. It's covered in scratches, as if it had weathered many storms.

data.name: QBZ-191
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Qiongjiu. Modified based on her combat preferences. Features increased firing stability and accuracy.

data.name: Golden Melody
data.description: A high-performance assault rifle assigned to Qiongjiu. Based on the QBZ-191. The adjustments ensure its versatility in various environments while enhancing its power and stability. Beneath its steady rhythm lies an unchanged purpose.

data.name: Retired Sportivo Calibro 12
data.description: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Severely worn out, it appears close to complete disrepair.

data.name: Sportivo Calibro 12
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Sabrina. Modified based on her combat preferences. Features lighter weight, making it easier to carry and use.

data.name: Mezzaluna
data.description: A high-performance shotgun assigned to Sabrina. Based on the Sportivo Calibro 12. Features a unique design that improves stability and makes the gun easier to store and carry while maintaining an intimidating appearance. To avoid frightening others, Sabrina named it after a common kitchen utensil from Italian cuisine.

data.name: Retired Nagant M1895
data.description: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Its surface is covered in rust, but it can still function after thorough maintenance.

data.name: Nagant M1895
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Nagant. Modified based on her combat preferences. Offers higher initial bullet velocity and improved durability.

data.name: Retired Type 95
data.description: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Its frame shows numerous repair marks but it still fires normally.

data.name: Type 95
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Daiyan. Modified based on her combat preferences. Features lighter weight and improved stability.

data.name: Heavy Strings
data.description: A high-performance assault rifle assigned to Daiyan. Based on the Type 95. Combines elegant appearance with destructive power. In Daiyan's hands, this "Heavy String" resonates like a deadly musical instrument.

data.name: Retired Sturmgewehr 36
data.description: A cheap weapon purchased from an underground broker. Poorly maintained, requiring a thorough inspection before use.

data.name: Sturmgewehr 36
data.description: A firearm highly compatible with Centaureissi. Modified based on her combat preferences. Features further reduced weight.

data.name: Maid's Rules
data.description: A high-performance assault rifle assigned to Centaureissi. Based on the Sturmgewehr 36 and crafted with materials of exceptional quality. As precise and refined as its owner, perfectly suited for its duties. It embodies the wielder's convictions and principles.
